OL,3,C'He absolutely loved life' say parents
OL,4,Cof student killed by a drug driver
OL,6,FDescribing the impact losing their son
OL,7,Fhas had on the whole family Mrs Pryde
OL,8,Fsaid: "We try and tell the kids that
OL,9,Fthey're allowed to be happy, they're
OL,10,Fallowed to make new memories and
OL,11,FOliver would want them to, but that's
OL,12,Fvery difficult even for us.
OL,14,F"Parenting whilst you're broken
OL,15,Fyourself is one of the hardest things
OL,16,Fyou can do. The kids idolised their
OL,17,Fbig brother, they miss him everyday,
OL,18,Fit's very difficult."
